Maybe a script could be set to release a random subset of the documents <i>and</i> delete another random subset, i.e.<p><pre><code>    if snowden_has_not_logged_in_for_7_days():
        for doc in documents:
            if random.choice([True, False]):
                release(doc)
            else:
                permanently_delete(doc)
</code></pre>
Then all parties have something to lose (either undesired leak of some document, or losing the chance to learn the contents of a document) if Snowden dies.
